         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne botanic Gardens ¶ July 16th 1863 ¶ Sir ¶  ¶ I have the honor to inform you that at a meeting of the Trustees of the Royal Park held this day T. Sumner Esq. in the Chair, a letter of the hono...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">63.07.16a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To James McCulloch</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A345 Royal Park Zoological Society letter and minute book, pp. 7-8, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne botanic Gardens</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">July 16th 1863</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to inform you that at a meeting of the Trustees of the Royal Park held this day T. Sumner Esq. in the Chair, a letter of the honorable the Chief Secretary, dated April 30 1863 and numbered 16[7]0<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont"
                             style="font-weight: bold; background-color: #FFFF00; ">is this letter at PRO or are all outward from 1863 missing?</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was submitted by the Acting President of the Acclimation Society expressing the acquiescence of the Government in the sale of the Dromedaries as proposed by the Council of the Acclim. Society. As no previous official intimation of the proposed sale of these animals was made by the Acclimation Council to the Trustees, my colleagues deemed it their duty to direct me to solicit your information, wether they can regard themselves as entirely relieved of any responsibility in reference to the sale of the Camels<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">At a meeting of the Trustees of Royal Park, Melbourne, on 16 July 1863, M 'stated, that he had as honorary Secretary deemed it his duty to summon his colleagues, in order that an opportunity might be afforded to them of expressing an opinion<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">wether</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>cognizance should be taken of the sale of the Dromedaries as proposed by the Council of the Acclimation Society and of which proposition no intimation had been given to the Trustees. Letters on the subject from W. Wardell Esq and Clem. Hodgkinson Esq. were read deprecating the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">inteded</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>sale of those useful animals. After a lengthened deliberation it was resolved that the honorary Secretary should apply to the honorable the Chief Secretary for information<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="background-color: #FFFF00; ">wether</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Trustees might regard themselves perfectly free of any responsibility of this transaction.' (A345, p. 123).</seg>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="color: #0070C0; ">The trustees also wrote to the Acclimatisation Society disputing the principles in the Society's letter to the Trustees, (M to W. Archer, 17 July 1863 (in this edition as 63-07-17a). See notes thereto.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient &amp; humble servt</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>F. M.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 2.4166in; text-indent: -0.6666in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hon. Secret to the Trustees of the</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 2.4166in; text-indent: -0.6666in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Park</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">The honorable the Chief Secretary</p>
         </div>
